---
/**
 * Team page: competencies and engagement model (EN).
 *
 * Business goal: show that clients can engage us for a single implementation phase or for the full end-to-end journey.
 * Layout mirrors PL: hero + cards + phases + imagery + TechStackMarquee.
 */
import MarketingLayout from '../../../layouts/MarketingLayout.astro';
import TechStackMarquee from '../../../components/TechStackMarquee.astro';
import { canonicalUrl } from '../../../lib/seo/site';
import { routeMap } from '../../../lib/i18n/routes';

const pathname = '/en/team/';
const title = 'Team - get2software.com';
const description =
  'The get2software product and implementation team: competencies from discovery to post-go-live support. We help clients in a chosen implementation phase or across the full process — integrations, cloud, ERP, quality, and evolution of operational systems.';

const imgHero = '/images/team/hero-team.jpg';
const imgPlanning = '/images/team/phase-planning.jpg';
const imgDelivery = '/images/team/delivery-collab.jpg';
---

<MarketingLayout
  locale="en"
  title={title}
  description={description}
  pathname={pathname}
  hreflangPl={canonicalUrl(routeMap.team.pl)}
  hreflangEn={canonicalUrl(pathname)}
  alternateHref={routeMap.team.pl}
  active="team"
  structuredData={[
    {
      '@context': 'https://schema.org',
      '@type': 'AboutPage',
      name: title,
      url: canonicalUrl(pathname)
    }
  ]}
>
  <div class="g2-container space-y-14 py-14 md:space-y-20 md:py-20">
    <header class="grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-2 lg:items-center">
      <div>
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-g2-accent">Team</p>
        <h1 class="g2-heading-xl mt-3 text-balance">We support you where you need us most</h1>
        <div class="g2-prose mt-6 max-w-xl space-y-4">
          <p class="!mt-0">
            We design and implement operational software for processes that must be accountable and ERP-ready. You can
            bring us in for <strong>a single phase</strong> — or ask us to lead <strong>the full journey</strong> from
            discovery to post-go-live operations.
          </p>
          <p>
            That lets us match skills to your situation: sometimes you need integrations and architecture first,
            sometimes a fast path to launch and operational support.
          </p>
        </div>
        <a href={routeMap.contact.en} class="g2-btn-primary mt-8 inline-flex">Discuss the scope</a>
      </div>
      <div
        class="not-prose overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-g2-glass-border bg-g2-surface shadow-g2-card"
        data-layout="team-hero-visual"
      >
        <img
          src={imgHero}
          alt="Team collaborating at computers — teamwork and delivery"
          width={1600}
          height={1067}
          class="aspect-[4/3] w-full object-cover"
          loading="eager"
          decoding="async"
        />
      </div>
    </header>

    <section aria-labelledby="team-how-heading" class="max-w-3xl">
      <h2 id="team-how-heading" class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-g2-text md:text-3xl">
        How we work
      </h2>
      <div class="g2-prose mt-4 space-y-4">
        <p>
          We combine business, architecture, and implementation perspectives. That lets us enter a project
          <strong>point-to-point</strong> (for example integrations, quality, rollout) or <strong>own the full chain</strong>
          from refining the process to post-go-live maintenance and evolution.
        </p>
        <p>
          We do not sell a licence alone — we work as a team accountable for operational outcomes: data that closes work in
          the field, reporting, and settlement with ERP.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="team-skills-heading" class="space-y-8">
      <h2 id="team-skills-heading" class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-g2-text md:text-3xl">
        Team competencies
      </h2>
      <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
        <article class="g2-glass p-6">
          <h3 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-g2-text">Discovery and process</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-g2-muted">
            We translate operations into requirements: roles, statuses, costs, exceptions — so the system supports the
            real workflow, not the other way around.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="g2-glass p-6">
          <h3 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-g2-text">Architecture and integrations</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-g2-muted">
            We design module boundaries and integration with ERP and neighbouring systems (APIs, queues, exports) —
            thinking about long-term maintenance and change.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="g2-glass p-6">
          <h3 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-g2-text">Development and quality</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-g2-muted">
            We build operational software with stability, auditability, and testable change — the foundation for
            multi-site rollouts.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="g2-glass p-6">
          <h3 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-g2-text">Rollout and training</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-g2-muted">
            We run go-live: configuration, data migration, pilot, communication with users — so day one is predictable
            for operations.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="g2-glass p-6">
          <h3 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-g2-text">Cloud and operations</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-g2-muted">
            We support hosting and post-go-live operations: incidents, changes, feature growth where the process expands.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="g2-glass p-6">
          <h3 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-g2-text">Security and compliance</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-g2-muted">
            We design with data separation, accountability, and alignment to client IT policies — especially in B2B and
            distributed teams.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Implementation phases: formal tone; each card max two sentences (substance without wall of text). -->
    <section aria-labelledby="team-phases-heading" class="g2-section-band -mx-4 px-4 py-14 sm:-mx-6 sm:px-6 lg:-mx-8 lg:px-8">
      <div class="g2-container !px-0">
        <h2 id="team-phases-heading" class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-g2-text md:text-3xl">
          Where we can support you
        </h2>
        <p class="g2-prose mt-4 max-w-3xl">
          Engagement may cover a single phase or the full programme — scope, ownership, and the collaboration model with IT
          and business stakeholders are agreed upfront and captured in project documentation.
        </p>

        <ol class="mt-10 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4">
          <li class="g2-glass p-5">
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-g2-accent">01</p>
            <p class="mt-2 font-display text-lg font-semibold text-g2-text">Discovery</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-g2-muted">
              We align business and operational goals and map the process: roles, statuses, exceptions, and ERP touchpoints.
              We capture risks, success criteria, an initial MVP scope, and integration dependencies across neighbouring systems.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li class="g2-glass p-5">
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-g2-accent">02</p>
            <p class="mt-2 font-display text-lg font-semibold text-g2-text">Solution design</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-g2-muted">
              We design module boundaries, the data model, and integration contracts (APIs, queues, files) for the agreed process.
              We prepare a delivery plan, acceptance test scenarios, and a clear definition of production readiness.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li class="g2-glass p-5">
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-g2-accent">03</p>
            <p class="mt-2 font-display text-lg font-semibold text-g2-text">Build and integrations</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-g2-muted">
              We deliver development, ERP integrations, and regression testing focused on stability and operational data consistency.
              We prepare rollout: environments, release sequencing, and support boundaries for go-live and stabilisation.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li class="g2-glass p-5">
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-g2-accent">04</p>
            <p class="mt-2 font-display text-lg font-semibold text-g2-text">Rollout and production go-live</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-g2-muted">
              We run pilot and production cutover against agreed quality gates for data and exception handling.
              We hand over documentation, training materials, and agreements for maintenance and evolution after go-live.
            </p>
          </li>
        </ol>

        <div class="mt-8 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
          <div class="g2-glass p-6">
            <p class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-g2-text">Post-go-live support</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-g2-muted">
              We provide operational maintenance, process-driven changes, and feature growth as the organisation scales.
              SLA priorities, channels, and escalation paths are tailored to process criticality and the client-side operating model.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="g2-glass p-6">
            <p class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-g2-text">Support in a selected area</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-g2-muted">
              When an in-house team is already in place, we can support a focused area — for example integrations, pre-go-live testing, or readiness reviews.
              Scope, timeline, and responsibility boundaries are agreed and documented for each engagement.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section
      aria-labelledby="team-visuals-heading"
      class="grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-2 lg:items-center"
      data-layout="team-visual-split"
    >
      <div class="not-prose order-2 overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-g2-glass-border bg-g2-surface shadow-g2-card lg:order-1">
        <img
          src={imgPlanning}
          alt="Team workshop planning a project — scope and timeline alignment"
          width={1600}
          height={1067}
          class="aspect-[4/3] w-full object-cover"
          loading="lazy"
          decoding="async"
        />
      </div>
      <div class="g2-prose order-1 max-w-xl lg:order-2">
        <h2 id="team-visuals-heading" class="!mt-0 text-balance font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-g2-text">
          Working with your organisation
        </h2>
        <p>
          We adapt the collaboration model to project scale — from intensive discovery to phased rollouts. What matters
          is that <strong>one team owns data consistency</strong> between field work, the operational system, and ERP —
          whether we join for a single phase or the full path.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-2 lg:items-center" data-layout="team-visual-split-2">
      <div class="g2-prose max-w-xl">
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-g2-text">From decision to stable operations</h2>
        <p>
          A strong implementation is not only code — it is communication, training, and keeping data clean after go-live.
          That is why our team behaves like an <strong>implementation partner</strong>, not a one-off vendor.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-g2-glass-border bg-g2-surface shadow-g2-card">
        <img
          src={imgDelivery}
          alt="Handshake in an office — closing agreements and partnership"
          width={1600}
          height={1067}
          class="aspect-[4/3] w-full object-cover"
          loading="lazy"
          decoding="async"
        />
      </div>
    </section>

    <TechStackMarquee locale="en" />

    <footer class="max-w-3xl space-y-6 border-t border-g2-border pt-10 not-prose">
      <p class="g2-prose text-g2-muted">
        Want to discuss a single phase, a full programme, or reinforcement in a specific area? Get in touch — we will
        propose a scope that fits your organisation and process.
      </p>
      <a href={routeMap.contact.en} class="g2-btn-primary inline-flex">Contact</a>
    </footer>

    <p class="pb-2 pt-8 text-xs text-g2-muted">
      Illustration photos:
      <a href="https://unsplash.com/license" class="text-g2-accent underline-offset-2 hover:underline" rel="noopener">
        Unsplash License
      </a>
      — source: Unsplash.
    </p>
  </div>
</MarketingLayout>
